When I visited the hotel on August 2019, it has only been 4 months since the opening. I could see that everything is new and fresh. The room is ibis standard, it met my expectation. However, there are 2 problems during my stay.
1. Power in my room was totally turned off twice. Had to wait engineer staff quite a while when it first happened on my first day. On my second day, they came faster. Anyway, it's a new hotel, thus I totally understand this technical problem.
2. Internet speed is not what I expected from a hotel in central Jakarta.

For the service, It was really good. All staff from security, front desk, f&b staff & housekeeping were courteous, polite and smiling. Thank you guys for that. Here are 3 names worth mentioning:
1. Jessie (FO Supervisor). She recognized my Accor Gold Status, but unfortunately the room upgrade was not available during my stay. But she directly extended my key card for late check out on my departure day, although I didn't really need that:-)
2. Jessyca (FO Staff). When I complained about the power in my room, she handled it really well. Around one hour after that, she called me to make sure that everything is OK.
3. Sulfitrah (MOD from FB). I only told him that the chicken might not be cooked thoroughly, I didn't expect anything afterwards, but instead he took it seriously and care enough to apologize which exceeded my expectation. Thank you for that. I wish you success for career in hospitality industry!

Beau séjour avec le détail de ma notation.

- Propreté rime avec entretien du mobilier - attention à votre maintenance
- Frigo existant dans la chambre mais vide
